1
00:00:01,940 --> 00:00:03,710
None of this is adding up.

2
00:00:04,710 --> 00:00:07,150
I have to go to the accident scene
first thing tomorrow.

3
00:00:07,210 --> 00:00:08,810
Don't go alone. Let's go together.

4
00:00:08,810 --> 00:00:11,220
And about that composite sketch,

5
00:00:11,420 --> 00:00:15,050
when my mom saw the sketch,
she screamed that he looked terrifying.

6
00:00:15,390 --> 00:00:16,650
After seeing the sketch?

7
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:19,820
Yes. It happened at our store,

8
00:00:19,890 --> 00:00:22,690
and also at the funeral home
when she saw Manager Lee.

9
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:24,830
What if...

10
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,930
the sketch is of Manager Lee?

11
00:00:28,070 --> 00:00:29,200
Manager Lee?

12
00:00:30,340 --> 00:00:33,670
If your mother was scared of Manager Lee,
we need to look into it right away.

13
00:00:33,910 --> 00:00:38,340
But wouldn't that be rude?
What if it's just a misunderstanding?

14
00:00:38,410 --> 00:00:40,040
Either way, I have to confront him.

15
00:00:40,550 --> 00:00:43,050
Besides, I have things to ask him
about the Dream Hotel CCTV footage.

16
00:00:49,050 --> 00:00:51,360
Hello, Manager Lee. It's Kang Baek Ho.

17
00:00:52,620 --> 00:00:56,430
I heard the police came by
to ask for your alibi.

18
00:00:58,030 --> 00:00:59,030
That's right.

19
00:00:59,430 --> 00:01:00,730
Why do you ask?

20
00:01:00,800 --> 00:01:02,130
I'm just curious.

21
00:01:02,930 --> 00:01:05,000
I just can't stand not knowing things.

22
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:08,340
What could you possibly be
so curious about now?

23
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:11,110
The police were just here poking around.

24
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:12,840
It's about the CCTV.

25
00:01:14,650 --> 00:01:16,410
It just doesn't make any sense to me.

26
00:01:17,150 --> 00:01:21,550
How can the CCTV in a hotel this large
be down due to a malfunction?

27
00:01:23,460 --> 00:01:24,560
Well...

28
00:01:24,990 --> 00:01:27,460
You mean how it was off for a few hours
in the parking garage?

29
00:01:28,530 --> 00:01:29,930
Things like that happen all the time.

30
00:01:30,530 --> 00:01:32,100
I suppose you wouldn't know.

31
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:33,730
It happens all the time?

32
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:37,040
Aren't you being a little too casual
about this?

33
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:41,410
All right. I understand.

34
00:01:42,240 --> 00:01:43,410
Thanks for the coffee.

35
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:46,580
Next time, it will be on me.

36
00:02:00,960 --> 00:02:03,860
Hey, who does this look like to you?

37
00:02:04,600 --> 00:02:06,760
I told you,
I can't tell who it is from this.

38
00:02:08,230 --> 00:02:10,070
Why did you even get this sketch made?

39
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:13,640
Are you doing this just to prove
Kang Baek Ho's father is innocent?

40
00:02:13,710 --> 00:02:15,110
That's not it.

41
00:02:15,110 --> 00:02:17,610
Then why do you keep shoving this sketch
in my face?

42
00:02:17,610 --> 00:02:21,750
Mom screamed when she saw this sketch
and said it was terrifying.

43
00:02:22,110 --> 00:02:24,250
Just like the last time
she saw Manager Lee.

44
00:02:25,050 --> 00:02:26,220
Manager Lee?

45
00:02:26,620 --> 00:02:30,390
Don't you think it kind of looks
like Manager Lee?

46
00:02:31,190 --> 00:02:33,660
I guess it does, a little.

47
00:02:35,190 --> 00:02:36,590
No way.

48
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:40,430
Think about how good CEO Chae
has been to us.

49
00:02:40,930 --> 00:02:43,300
Why would Manager Lee get Dad drunk?

50
00:02:44,540 --> 00:02:45,540
That's ridiculous.

51
00:02:47,110 --> 00:02:49,670
You're right.
He must just be a look-alike.

52
00:03:00,290 --> 00:03:02,120
I really don't want to go see Mom.

53
00:03:02,790 --> 00:03:04,760
Ma Seo Rin, be careful.

54
00:03:05,190 --> 00:03:07,590
You can't go in there
and start nitpicking for answers.

55
00:03:08,260 --> 00:03:12,330
I hope Mom is not the one
trying to kill Oh Jang Mi.

56
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:15,870
Jun Ho!

57
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:26,110
Jun Ho...

58
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:30,650
It's not Jun Ho.

59
00:03:31,420 --> 00:03:32,750
It's General Manager Kang Jun Ho.

60
00:03:34,790 --> 00:03:37,120
Were you upset I didn't use your title?

61
00:03:37,390 --> 00:03:39,560
Okay. General Manager Kang.

62
00:03:40,060 --> 00:03:42,130
You just made my heart skip a beat.

63
00:03:42,290 --> 00:03:43,560
How about we hug just one more time?

64
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,060
There you go again.

65
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,870
You realize this is almost harassment?

66
00:03:47,930 --> 00:03:48,970
No.

67
00:03:51,270 --> 00:03:53,640
I'm feeling down today.
Let's go get a drink.

68
00:03:54,070 --> 00:03:56,540
- My treat. Okay?
- No, thank you.

69
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:59,780
Where to, General Manager Kang?

70
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,910
I'm on my way to see CEO Chae. Why?

71
00:04:03,150 --> 00:04:04,920
Okay, then have a good meeting.

72
00:04:13,560 --> 00:04:14,560
Yes?

73
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:18,700
Come on in, General Manager Kang.

74
00:04:19,300 --> 00:04:20,630
I heard your interview went well.

75
00:04:21,130 --> 00:04:22,130
Have a seat.

76
00:04:23,970 --> 00:04:26,600
I called for Seo Rin, too.
I wanted to talk when you were both here.

77
00:04:27,010 --> 00:04:28,540
I just ran into her out front.

78
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,540
She didn't seem
to be heading this way, though.

79
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,080
Is that so?

80
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,150
I wonder what she's up to.

81
00:04:35,010 --> 00:04:36,380
Is something wrong?

82
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:38,720
No, it's nothing.

83
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:41,750
Anyway, the reason I asked to see you...

84
00:04:42,350 --> 00:04:44,420
was to check if the meeting preparations
were coming along...

85
00:04:44,420 --> 00:04:47,230
and if there was anything
I could do to help.

86
00:04:47,330 --> 00:04:48,560
Just get to the point.

87
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:51,200
All right. I won't beat around the bush.

88
00:04:53,870 --> 00:04:57,800
How would you feel
if Team Leader Jin became your boss?

89
00:04:58,470 --> 00:04:59,640
Team Leader Jin Hong Ju?

90
00:04:59,970 --> 00:05:01,970
The Chairman has declared
that he's taking Jin Hong Ju's mother...

91
00:05:02,370 --> 00:05:04,610
to be his wife.

92
00:05:05,080 --> 00:05:08,180
Of course, on the condition
that it won't be a legal marriage.

93
00:05:08,510 --> 00:05:10,150
But do you think Team Leader Jin
and her mother will settle for that?

94
00:05:10,820 --> 00:05:14,320
Now that they're becoming family,
Team Leader Jin's status will change.

95
00:05:17,660 --> 00:05:18,990
So, with that said...

96
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:20,630
General Manager Kang.

97
00:05:22,690 --> 00:05:24,830
Can I consider you to be on my side now?

98
00:05:33,140 --> 00:05:34,810
What do you say to marrying Seo Rin...

99
00:05:36,310 --> 00:05:37,880
and taking over Dream for yourself?

100
00:05:39,210 --> 00:05:40,550
You want me...

101
00:05:41,710 --> 00:05:42,710
to marry Director Ma?

102
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,280
That's right.

103
00:05:45,480 --> 00:05:48,250
Seo Rin grew up without a father
or any siblings.

104
00:05:48,350 --> 00:05:51,520
All she's ever known is
Chairman Ma's doting affection.

105
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:53,120
You know how it is.

106
00:05:53,490 --> 00:05:55,690
A grandfather just can't help
but spoil his granddaughter.

107
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:59,400
Seo Rin might be acting childish
on purpose...

108
00:05:59,730 --> 00:06:02,270
to hide how lonely she is.

109
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,540
Hiding it?
That's not how it looks to me at all.

110
00:06:06,970 --> 00:06:09,910
Don't you think it's just that
she's bad at expressing her feelings?

111
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,710
I think...

112
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:16,610
you could really soothe Seo Rin's heart.

113
00:06:17,220 --> 00:06:19,680
- What do you say?
- I must be hearing things.

114
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:23,320
This is absurd.

115
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,360
You were so dead set against me,

116
00:06:25,820 --> 00:06:27,760
so what's with the sudden change of heart?

117
00:06:28,460 --> 00:06:30,330
Me? Marry Director Ma?

118
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:31,760
Like I said,

119
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:35,900
Seo Rin and I absolutely need you.

120
00:06:38,140 --> 00:06:40,510
Join us, General Manager Kang.

121
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:42,540
Why me, of all people?

122
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:47,650
I need you because you're competent
and a great asset to this company.

123
00:06:48,750 --> 00:06:51,720
If you join forces with me
and marry my Seo Rin,

124
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:57,560
you will achieve everything
you've ever wanted.

125
00:06:58,390 --> 00:07:00,060
Do you even know what my dream is?

126
00:07:02,890 --> 00:07:03,900
I think I have an idea.

127
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:06,930
To climb to the very top.

128
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:10,800
To a position where
everyone has to look up to you.

129
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:12,440
Am I wrong?

130
00:07:21,080 --> 00:07:23,510
Seo Rin. Are you just getting home?

131
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:25,350
Yes, Grandpa.

132
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:30,790
Jin Hong Ju.

133
00:07:31,360 --> 00:07:33,760
You used to be my gofer, carrying my bags.

134
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,460
Now that you've moved up in the world,

135
00:07:35,590 --> 00:07:36,860
do you think you're untouchable?

136
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:40,800
What? Why are you being like this
all of a sudden?

137
00:07:41,030 --> 00:07:44,140
Seo Rin, Hong Ju is your aunt now.

138
00:07:44,470 --> 00:07:46,140
So you'd better watch your mouth. Got it?

139
00:07:47,610 --> 00:07:48,740
You've got to be kidding me.

140
00:07:48,840 --> 00:07:51,410
Hong Ju, you don't have to speak formally
to Seo Rin anymore.

141
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:55,150
You're her superior now. Got it?

142
00:07:55,610 --> 00:07:56,650
Okay.

143
00:07:58,050 --> 00:08:00,350
Father, that's all right with you,
isn't it?

144
00:08:01,420 --> 00:08:02,420
Of course.

145
00:08:03,790 --> 00:08:04,860
You heard him.

146
00:08:04,860 --> 00:08:07,560
Grandpa, people who come from nothing...

147
00:08:07,630 --> 00:08:09,960
can't handle it
when they suddenly come into money.

148
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:14,730
If you give our shares to those beggars,
I swear I'll disown you.

149
00:08:14,970 --> 00:08:17,440
Don't give them a single cent.
I've made myself clear.

150
00:08:19,940 --> 00:08:22,510
My word. Goodness, I feel faint.

151
00:08:23,610 --> 00:08:26,380
She called us beggars!

152
00:08:32,620 --> 00:08:34,820
How am I going to crush
that tramp, Ma Seo Rin?

153
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:36,890
There's no need to get upset.

154
00:08:36,890 --> 00:08:38,690
All we have to do is hold the ceremony.

155
00:08:39,020 --> 00:08:41,430
No matter how much they kick and scream,

156
00:08:41,630 --> 00:08:46,130
half of the Chairman's shares
are destined to be ours.

157
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,470
You're right, Mom.

158
00:08:47,670 --> 00:08:50,070
No matter how much Ma Seo Rin struggles,

159
00:08:50,400 --> 00:08:51,870
that ship has already sailed.

160
00:08:51,870 --> 00:08:53,400
That's right.

161
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:56,570
I'm Chairman Ma's daughter now.

162
00:08:56,970 --> 00:08:58,210
I should buy myself some nice clothes.

163
00:08:58,210 --> 00:08:59,910
Of course.

164
00:08:59,910 --> 00:09:01,380
You need to look the part.

165
00:09:01,610 --> 00:09:02,850
Let's go shopping tomorrow.

166
00:09:03,750 --> 00:09:06,780
By the way,
why haven't I heard from Madam Kim?

167
00:09:07,550 --> 00:09:11,460
I told her to find
the best possible husband for you.

168
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,760
What about a lawyer for a husband?

169
00:09:14,430 --> 00:09:16,930
You know, his mom's a lawyer,
and his dad's a professor.

170
00:09:16,990 --> 00:09:19,360
Do you think the Chairman would approve
of a husband like that?

171
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:23,670
You need to marry the son of a tycoon
who can help our Dream Group.

172
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:25,470
Why are you being so shortsighted?

173
00:09:27,170 --> 00:09:28,170
Don't tell me...

174
00:09:29,070 --> 00:09:31,910
Are you talking about that punk,
Lawyer Kang Baek Ho?

175
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:34,950
- Why would you call Baek Ho a punk?
- Hey, Jin Hong Ju!

176
00:09:35,210 --> 00:09:37,210
Come on, get a grip!

177
00:09:42,320 --> 00:09:46,660
In the first trial,
stress the victim's pedestrian negligence.

178
00:09:47,220 --> 00:09:49,430
You got the hospital's consent
to check the blood sample taken...

179
00:09:49,830 --> 00:09:51,430
during Oh Bok Gil's surgery, right?

180
00:09:52,330 --> 00:09:53,330
Yes, here.

181
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,700
I confirmed it with the police's consent.

182
00:09:56,230 --> 00:09:59,770
A blood alcohol content of 0.12 percent
means he was heavily intoxicated.

183
00:10:00,440 --> 00:10:02,640
It's key evidence for proving
the victim's negligence,

184
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:06,380
so make sure it's on the initial list
of evidence with the forensics report.

185
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:09,650
I can't believe
I have to go up against Jang Mi.

186
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:13,020
I know that for a fact
her father isn't the kind of man...

187
00:10:13,350 --> 00:10:14,620
who would be on the road, dead drunk.

188
00:10:18,990 --> 00:10:19,990
Dad, by any chance,

189
00:10:20,660 --> 00:10:21,990
have you seen this person before?

190
00:10:22,730 --> 00:10:23,730
What?

191
00:10:26,860 --> 00:10:28,630
Who is this?

192
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:32,200
He bought soju near the scene
of Jang Mi's father's accident,

193
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:35,040
and something about him
seems suspicious to me.

194
00:10:35,170 --> 00:10:36,970
What's so suspicious about him?

195
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:40,240
I feel like he's somehow connected
to the accident.

196
00:10:40,750 --> 00:10:42,680
- He might even be the culprit.
- Kang Baek Ho.

197
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:44,450
Are you suggesting that this man...

198
00:10:44,820 --> 00:10:48,390
pried open Oh Jang Mi's father's mouth
and forced soju down his throat?

199
00:10:48,690 --> 00:10:50,350
What could possibly be so suspicious?

200
00:10:50,690 --> 00:10:52,420
So what if he bought soju?

201
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:54,360
Don't people live in that neighborhood?

202
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:56,590
Does that make
everyone who buys soju a criminal?

203
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:01,230
I looked up the serial number
of the soju bottle found at the scene,

204
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:03,300
and it was from a batch sold nearby.

205
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:08,270
This is the closest store
to the accident scene.

206
00:11:08,570 --> 00:11:10,640
He most likely bought the soju here.

207
00:11:10,710 --> 00:11:12,540
And since this store is so remote,

208
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:15,580
I was told that almost no one
but the local residents shops there.

209
00:11:15,850 --> 00:11:18,050
The only person who bought soju
at that store that day...

210
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:20,520
(Case Summary, Yeongseo Police Chief)

211
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:21,690
was this man.

212
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,520
- Really?
- I will prove that Dad's accident...

213
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:27,660
wasn't what ultimately killed...

214
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:29,060
Jang Mi's father.

215
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:31,630
That's the only way Jang Mi's father
can rest in peace,

216
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:33,860
and you can clear your name, Dad.

217
00:11:34,170 --> 00:11:36,230
Your father never lost his honor
in the first place.

218
00:11:36,770 --> 00:11:38,600
How can he lose his honor
when he's innocent?

219
00:11:39,440 --> 00:11:41,070
Your father is completely innocent.

220
00:11:41,810 --> 00:11:42,810
Mom, come on.

221
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:52,920
By the way, Kang Hyuk.

222
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:55,220
What did you do with the wrench?

223
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:56,890
I buried it on a nearby mountain.

224
00:11:57,420 --> 00:11:58,420
On a mountain?

225
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:00,220
He buried it on a mountain?

226
00:12:01,430 --> 00:12:02,530
A mountain?

227
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:07,830
Even if I knew which one,
how could I search an entire mountain?

228
00:12:08,370 --> 00:12:10,300
I can't even stand getting my shoes dirty.

229
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,500
Gosh, I don't know.

230
00:12:14,810 --> 00:12:16,170
No.

231
00:12:16,170 --> 00:12:17,210
But...

232
00:12:17,740 --> 00:12:20,410
that wrench seems like it could be
the crucial piece of evidence.

233
00:12:22,050 --> 00:12:23,780
Bok Gil is gone.

234
00:12:24,620 --> 00:12:27,890
Jang Mi.
Let's go see Bok Gil at the hospital.

235
00:12:28,650 --> 00:12:32,390
Mom, Dad said he was really tired.

236
00:12:32,790 --> 00:12:34,360
He needs to get some sleep,

237
00:12:35,060 --> 00:12:37,130
so let's go see him later. Okay?

238
00:12:41,430 --> 00:12:43,330
Jang Mi, take a look at this.

239
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:46,140
Okay. What are these plane tickets for?

240
00:12:48,310 --> 00:12:49,370
So this is it.

241
00:12:50,340 --> 00:12:52,380
This is why Dad wanted to meet CEO Chae.

242
00:12:53,140 --> 00:12:56,010
He knew I’d refuse to go abroad to study
if he was the one sending me.

243
00:12:56,680 --> 00:12:59,050
He was going to ask her to say
that she was sponsoring me instead.

244
00:12:59,420 --> 00:13:01,020
That's why he went to see her.

245
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:03,250
Because all these dangerous things
kept happening to you,

246
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,690
he must have thought
sending you away would be safer.

247
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:10,360
What do I do? Tae Pyung, I think
I'm the one who caused Dad's death.

248
00:13:11,460 --> 00:13:13,530
I miss Bok Gil.

249
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:16,300
Bok Gil, please hurry back.

250
00:13:16,930 --> 00:13:21,310
I miss him so much, Bok Gil.

251
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:24,710
Bok Gil.

252
00:13:25,310 --> 00:13:27,880
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

253
00:13:33,050 --> 00:13:34,120
Mom.

254
00:13:35,450 --> 00:13:36,820
What are we going to do now?

255
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:40,520
You're going to keep crying
and asking for Dad.

256
00:13:42,060 --> 00:13:43,890
What am I supposed to do
every time that happens?

257
00:14:02,650 --> 00:14:05,480
Dad treasured all these memories.

258
00:14:06,850 --> 00:14:08,020
I'm so sorry, Dad.

259
00:14:08,890 --> 00:14:10,090
I'm so sorry.

260
00:14:10,690 --> 00:14:11,690
I'm so very sorry.

261
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,930
I will find out why you had to die,

262
00:14:16,590 --> 00:14:18,100
no matter what.

263
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,900
And the person you were always
searching for,

264
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:24,240
the one who did this to Mom.

265
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,040
I'll find them.

266
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:30,040
I'll do it so you can finally
rest in peace.

267
00:14:32,710 --> 00:14:34,140
I love you, Dad.

268
00:14:45,460 --> 00:14:46,460
Mrs. Yang.

269
00:14:48,760 --> 00:14:51,330
- Where's Seo Rin?
- She left for work early this morning.

270
00:14:51,530 --> 00:14:53,360
She went to work early this morning?

271
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:56,930
Is something wrong with Seo Rin?

272
00:14:58,100 --> 00:15:00,000
- What?
- It's just that...

273
00:15:00,340 --> 00:15:03,170
she rushed in here yesterday afternoon,
all worked up,

274
00:15:03,270 --> 00:15:05,910
grabbed something,
and then left again right away.

275
00:15:06,480 --> 00:15:08,150
Seo Rin hasn't been herself lately...

276
00:15:08,550 --> 00:15:10,480
and seems out of her mind. It's strange.

277
00:15:11,750 --> 00:15:13,520
She's causing trouble again.

278
00:15:14,290 --> 00:15:15,650
Where in the world did she go?

279
00:15:17,490 --> 00:15:18,490
By the way,

280
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:22,030
where are you getting the money
to dress up like this?

281
00:15:22,190 --> 00:15:25,160
What's that supposed to mean?
Like mother, like daughter, I see.

282
00:15:25,530 --> 00:15:28,200
Are you trying to treat us like beggars,
just like Seo Rin did?

283
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:32,070
- Isn't all that money from Dream Group?
- No, it's not!

284
00:15:32,470 --> 00:15:34,710
I used the credit card my husband gave me.

285
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:39,110
Don't play dumb.
You're using Father's card.

286
00:15:39,610 --> 00:15:42,610
Anyway, it must be nice
being such an airhead.

287
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:49,050
I am your mother-in-law.
I told you to show me some respect.

288
00:15:49,390 --> 00:15:51,320
How could you forget so quickly?

289
00:15:52,720 --> 00:15:54,120
The test results are in.

290
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:56,260
I'll give you a moment.

291
00:16:07,370 --> 00:16:08,940
(Ma Seo Rin and Chae Hwa Young
are not biologically related.)

292
00:16:09,010 --> 00:16:11,680
Shit. I'm not my mother's daughter?

293
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:14,180
Then who am I?

294
00:16:16,050 --> 00:16:18,050
(Genos Gene Examination Center)

295
00:16:19,780 --> 00:16:22,550
(Ma Seo Rin and Oh Jang Mi
are 99.998 percent biologically related.)

296
00:16:22,850 --> 00:16:24,490
I'm related to Oh Jang Mi?

297
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:27,420
That must mean we're twins.

298
00:16:28,330 --> 00:16:31,030
No way. How could this have happened?

299
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:37,530
How can I not be my mother's daughter?

300
00:16:38,670 --> 00:16:40,700
Then who is my real mother,

301
00:16:41,810 --> 00:16:42,940
the one who gave birth to me?

302
00:16:43,740 --> 00:16:46,610
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

303
00:16:48,510 --> 00:16:51,220
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

304
00:16:51,820 --> 00:16:53,180
You're not Jang Mi.

305
00:16:53,980 --> 00:16:55,390
You're pretending to be Jang Mi.

306
00:16:55,450 --> 00:16:57,790
- You're not Jang Mi.
- What's with this woman?

307
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:01,590
That woman is my mother?

308
00:17:02,190 --> 00:17:05,200
No, this is all a huge mistake.

309
00:17:07,870 --> 00:17:10,370
- Mom.
- Hey, Jang Mi.

310
00:17:10,430 --> 00:17:13,300
- What's this?
- A package came for you.

311
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:16,040
- Jang Mi...
- Oh Jang Mi, who looks exactly like me,

312
00:17:17,070 --> 00:17:19,110
just called that woman "Mom."

313
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:22,050
There's no way a woman like that
is my mother.

314
00:17:22,450 --> 00:17:24,620
Aren't you cold? Maybe I should've
put another jacket around you.

315
00:17:24,820 --> 00:17:26,350
It's okay.

316
00:17:26,350 --> 00:17:28,390
Something is completely wrong here.

317
00:17:28,690 --> 00:17:30,550
It's all a big mistake!

318
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:35,560
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

319
00:17:38,330 --> 00:17:40,630
Mom, you had a bad cold,

320
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:42,970
but you got better right away
after taking your medicine, didn't you?

321
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:45,270
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

322
00:17:46,040 --> 00:17:50,540
Mom, you need to make sure you bundle up
so you don't get sick again, okay?

323
00:17:51,780 --> 00:17:52,980
Jang Mi, you're so pretty.

324
00:17:53,780 --> 00:17:56,080
Jang Mi is Suk Hee's daughter.

325
00:17:57,310 --> 00:18:00,450
That's right. I'm your daughter, Mom.
My beautiful Mom.

326
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:02,990
I must have had it wrong from the start.

327
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:05,460
She's just some girl who looks like me.

328
00:18:06,360 --> 00:18:07,930
That's it. A doppelganger.

329
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:10,190
- Suk Hee...
- She has to be a doppelganger.

330
00:18:10,260 --> 00:18:11,800
- listens well.
- Shit.

331
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:13,730
Suk Hee isn't sick anymore.

332
00:18:15,270 --> 00:18:16,400
(Mom)

333
00:18:16,470 --> 00:18:19,070
- Mom, let's go get some ice cream.
- Oh, you're here!

334
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:21,140
- Go on, you two.
- We'll be back!

335
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:24,540
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

336
00:18:33,080 --> 00:18:36,420
- What?
- Seo Rin, you left early. Where are you?

337
00:18:36,750 --> 00:18:38,760
Why do you always have to be so nosy?
Shit.

338
00:18:38,820 --> 00:18:41,590
Is a mother checking on her daughter
considered nosy?

339
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:44,190
I only called
because I barely get to see you.

340
00:18:45,430 --> 00:18:47,730
How can I face you after all this, Mom?

341
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,630
Hello? Are you there?

342
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,970
Did you have something to say to me?

343
00:18:55,270 --> 00:18:56,840
I spoke with General Manager Kang
yesterday.

344
00:18:57,410 --> 00:18:58,640
I told him to marry you.

345
00:18:59,740 --> 00:19:02,110
- Are you serious?
- Of course I am.

346
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:04,880
So, start showing up
at the office regularly...

347
00:19:05,150 --> 00:19:08,120
and attending the meetings.
No more distractions.

348
00:19:08,650 --> 00:19:09,650
Fine.

349
00:19:15,630 --> 00:19:18,260
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

350
00:19:27,070 --> 00:19:29,240
- It's time for the meeting.
- All right.

351
00:19:31,780 --> 00:19:33,080
Today will be...

352
00:19:33,510 --> 00:19:36,010
our Jun Ho's first major presentation
in front of the Chairman.

353
00:19:36,310 --> 00:19:37,780
I wonder if he'll do okay.

354
00:19:37,850 --> 00:19:40,080
Ma'am, in front of others,

355
00:19:40,150 --> 00:19:42,290
you need to be careful
about saying "our Jun Ho."

356
00:19:42,850 --> 00:19:44,050
Oh, right.

357
00:19:44,890 --> 00:19:46,760
- Okay.
- Shall we?

358
00:19:48,290 --> 00:19:51,960
It includes the hotel's signature
red wine reduction sauce.

359
00:19:52,300 --> 00:19:53,300
Next.

360
00:19:54,060 --> 00:19:56,970
The Ocean Jewel Box.
Sauces include a spicy chili vinaigrette,

361
00:19:56,970 --> 00:20:00,940
mignonette, and aioli,
making up our signature trio of sauces.

362
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:05,480
That concludes my introduction
of our new signature dishes.

363
00:20:05,780 --> 00:20:07,910
- Now, for the next item...
- All right, that's enough.

364
00:20:08,710 --> 00:20:11,010
We can just read the handouts
for the rest.

365
00:20:11,550 --> 00:20:14,690
General Manager Kang, in your opinion,

366
00:20:15,420 --> 00:20:17,990
why do you think we hired you?

367
00:20:18,690 --> 00:20:22,830
I started from the very bottom
and worked my way up in the kitchen.

368
00:20:23,690 --> 00:20:25,260
My strengths are...

369
00:20:26,330 --> 00:20:28,600
reading people's tastes and emotions,
as well as quickly reading the room.

370
00:20:29,170 --> 00:20:32,540
I believe I have more hands-on,
practical experience than anyone else.

371
00:20:33,770 --> 00:20:34,770
Is that so?

372
00:20:35,270 --> 00:20:37,610
In that case,
what's the biggest problem...

373
00:20:37,610 --> 00:20:39,810
with Dream Hotel's
Food and Beverage Department?

374
00:20:39,980 --> 00:20:41,480
Instead of focusing on
customer satisfaction,

375
00:20:42,350 --> 00:20:45,120
I believe too much energy is spent
on procedures and reports.

376
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:48,290
To innovate, you have to focus
on the people.

377
00:20:48,650 --> 00:20:50,220
Both our guests and our staff.

378
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:52,620
You talk a good game.

379
00:20:53,060 --> 00:20:57,290
So, what, specifically,
are you going to change?

380
00:20:57,660 --> 00:21:00,730
First, I will establish
a new menu development team.

381
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:05,270
We'll create a channel for on-site staff
to share their diverse ideas.

382
00:21:05,340 --> 00:21:09,670
Second, I plan to redesign the hall layout
based on customer flow.

383
00:21:09,970 --> 00:21:12,480
Third, I'll conduct
a transparent review...

384
00:21:12,880 --> 00:21:14,440
of our price agreements
with current vendors.

385
00:21:15,580 --> 00:21:17,780
That's Jun Ho for you.

386
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:20,350
Alright.

387
00:21:21,620 --> 00:21:22,950
I expect you to back up...

388
00:21:23,790 --> 00:21:26,560
everything you've said with results.

389
00:21:27,520 --> 00:21:28,530
Yes, Chairman.

390
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,080
What's going on?

391
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:53,250
Why did my mom suddenly give Jun Ho
that look of affection?

392
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:56,350
Why's she suddenly pushing for my marriage
to Jun Ho?

393
00:21:57,320 --> 00:22:00,090
I wonder what Mom was thinking,
raising me as her daughter.

394
00:22:00,860 --> 00:22:03,130
Wait, we're twins.

395
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:05,760
Why was I the only one
she ended up raising?

396
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:13,240
I said that you don't have to do this.

397
00:22:13,870 --> 00:22:15,340
Come on, let me help.

398
00:22:15,610 --> 00:22:17,870
I just really want to help you,
even if it's just this.

399
00:22:18,180 --> 00:22:21,580
You doing this
isn't going to change anything.

400
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,050
You need onions peeled, right?

401
00:22:25,580 --> 00:22:28,020
I used to be a cook in the army.

402
00:22:28,420 --> 00:22:30,390
I'm an expert at peeling onions.

403
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:41,500
Hold on.

404
00:23:05,990 --> 00:23:06,990
Here.

405
00:23:08,560 --> 00:23:10,760
That's enough. Just go.

406
00:23:12,430 --> 00:23:13,930
Let me just finish this, and then I'll go.

407
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:29,580
What excuse should I use
to give this to Manager Lee?

408
00:23:33,420 --> 00:23:35,490
I have to find out everything
about my mother with this.

409
00:23:36,390 --> 00:23:37,490
If we're twins,

410
00:23:37,990 --> 00:23:40,660
why am I the daughter of a woman
I'm not even related to,

411
00:23:41,490 --> 00:23:43,690
and why was I separated from Oh Jang Mi?

412
00:23:44,730 --> 00:23:48,000
What about Oh Jang Mi's father's death?
And what's the wrench?

413
00:23:51,570 --> 00:23:54,840
I'm going to find out everything
with this bug.

414
00:24:04,820 --> 00:24:05,950
Mister.

415
00:24:07,180 --> 00:24:08,320
"Mister?"

416
00:24:09,450 --> 00:24:11,020
It’s been a while
since you last called me that.

417
00:24:12,090 --> 00:24:15,060
You've been parked for a while,
so I came to check on you.

418
00:24:15,730 --> 00:24:16,830
Is something wrong?

419
00:24:20,830 --> 00:24:21,870
What's that?

420
00:24:23,030 --> 00:24:25,200
I was going to give it to Jun Ho.

421
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:28,000
But then Mom gave Jun Ho a watch,

422
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,240
which totally spoiled it.

423
00:24:33,540 --> 00:24:34,540
Do you want it?

424
00:24:35,410 --> 00:24:36,680
Come to think of it,

425
00:24:36,680 --> 00:24:39,350
you were the only one
who looked out for me when I was little,

426
00:24:39,850 --> 00:24:41,420
and I've been so awful to you, haven't I?

427
00:24:42,590 --> 00:24:43,950
What are you talking about?

428
00:24:44,490 --> 00:24:46,890
Not at all.
You were adorable when you were little.

429
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:49,390
You're saying I'm not adorable anymore.

430
00:24:49,460 --> 00:24:51,930
I'd say you're more charismatic
than adorable.

431
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:53,500
You get it from CEO Chae.

432
00:24:56,300 --> 00:24:58,540
And here I thought
I took after my grandfather,

433
00:24:58,970 --> 00:25:01,640
but I guess you see my mother in me.

434
00:25:03,240 --> 00:25:04,910
Well, anyway...

435
00:25:05,380 --> 00:25:06,380
It's a gift.

436
00:25:07,410 --> 00:25:08,410
You're...

437
00:25:08,780 --> 00:25:11,580
- giving this to me?
- It was supposed to be a gift for Jun Ho,

438
00:25:11,880 --> 00:25:13,020
so I guess it's a little weird?

439
00:25:13,420 --> 00:25:16,450
If you don't like it, just toss it.
I was going to throw it out anyway.

440
00:25:22,330 --> 00:25:23,890
Seo Rin gave this to me.

441
00:25:24,590 --> 00:25:27,100
She said that it was for Jun Ho,
but you got him one first.

442
00:25:27,100 --> 00:25:28,270
Did she?

443
00:25:28,830 --> 00:25:30,100
That's sweet of her.

444
00:25:30,670 --> 00:25:34,540
Seo Rin was always fond of you,
calling you "Mister" and following you.

445
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:37,870
Keep up your good relationship
with Seo Rin.

446
00:25:38,140 --> 00:25:39,240
Yes, I understand.

447
00:25:40,810 --> 00:25:44,980
We still need to get rid of
Oh Jang Mi quickly, though.

448
00:25:45,180 --> 00:25:47,650
First, I'll make sure she's too busy
making ends meet.

449
00:25:47,650 --> 00:25:49,350
Then I'll find a way.

450
00:25:49,950 --> 00:25:51,860
It seems she's very behind
on her shop's rent.

451
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:54,590
All right.
Especially with her father dead,

452
00:25:54,860 --> 00:25:57,160
we need to make her so busy
just putting food on the table...

453
00:25:57,630 --> 00:25:59,700
that she can't think about anything else.

454
00:25:59,930 --> 00:26:02,170
She's going to get rid
of Oh Jang Mi quickly?

455
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:05,000
- What about the police?
- The investigation's been closed.

456
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:06,800
So the chief pulled some strings.

457
00:26:07,300 --> 00:26:08,640
All right, that's settled then.

458
00:26:09,170 --> 00:26:11,140
Now we just have to keep a close eye
on Seo Rin.

459
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:12,680
"Keep a close eye on me?"

460
00:26:12,940 --> 00:26:14,580
Yes. I'll make sure there are no slip-ups.

461
00:26:15,710 --> 00:26:19,550
Where has Seo Rin been running off to?
I haven't seen any sign of her lately.

462
00:26:19,880 --> 00:26:22,190
And what's all this nonsense
about a twin all of a sudden?

463
00:26:22,850 --> 00:26:26,890
She should be grateful
I stole her and not Oh Jang Mi.

464
00:26:27,590 --> 00:26:29,960
I'm the one
who lets her live like a princess.

465
00:26:30,590 --> 00:26:33,730
If I had taken Oh Jang Mi instead of her,

466
00:26:34,530 --> 00:26:36,000
she'd be the one suffering...

467
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,700
as Jung Suk Hee's daughter
right now, right?

468
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,600
I'm the one who changed her fate.

469
00:26:41,300 --> 00:26:43,640
And she repays me by running wild
with no sense of gratitude.

470
00:26:44,110 --> 00:26:45,680
She really gets on my nerves.

471
00:27:04,260 --> 00:27:06,000
(The First Man)

472
00:27:06,060 --> 00:27:07,500
Are you out of your mind?

473
00:27:07,500 --> 00:27:09,430
You want to make your father a murderer?

474
00:27:09,530 --> 00:27:10,770
Jun Ho!

475
00:27:10,970 --> 00:27:12,570
I just want to find the truth.

476
00:27:12,740 --> 00:27:15,070
This is my insurance policy, just in case.

477
00:27:15,370 --> 00:27:16,910
So, Mom wants to keep an eye on me?

478
00:27:16,910 --> 00:27:18,510
Fine. I'll be the one controlling her.

479
00:27:18,710 --> 00:27:20,980
You're giving CEO Chae a thank-you gift?

480
00:27:21,180 --> 00:27:23,280
Nothing I do makes me feel any better.

481
00:27:23,550 --> 00:27:25,450
How can she look exactly like me?

482
00:27:25,750 --> 00:27:27,720
What in the world is going on?

483
00:27:30,850 --> 00:27:32,820
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
